			<title>May 12, 2012 - Secrets of Ritual!</title>
            <link><![CDATA[http://secrets.libsyn.com/may-12-2012-secrets-of-ritual]]></link>
            <description><![CDATA[<p><span style="font-size: small;">We're going to be getting into some heavy stuff soon, but - no, wait we are indeeed already into some heavy stuff.&nbsp; Between what we saw on prayer last week and what we explore about ritual today, we're seen what makes up the most powerful rituals ever done!&nbsp; The difference is in the heart and will of the one who is doing the prayer or the ritual.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">And speaking of prayer, guess where ritual has its roots?&nbsp; In prayer that has a reputation of working.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">The formula is ancient and you've seen it elsewhere in other context since you were in school learning to write.&nbsp; The next step is to see what can be made with it, and what can be put into it.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Now, with this you are going to have an adventure, one that you might wish to write down for the sake of the memories you'll be having.&nbsp; And also, for that matter, for the results you will be seeing.</span></p>
