<p><span style="font-size: small;">Remember, this is not spirituality of the so-called "clockmaker theory" in which someone set things into motion and then stepped back to watch (and keep score on you and me). And this is also not about the mood-swinging deity of the people who keep talking about something called "God's will". &nbsp;No, we are talking about The Divine who cares, regardless of the name or names you or I use to refer to The Divine. &nbsp;And we're talking about The Divine who not only cares about us, but actually does things.</span></p>
