<p><span style="font-size: small;">A baby was born at Yule. &nbsp;We've seen him go through all of the stages of growing and coming of age, and the last Sabbat was Beltaine, where we celebrated his wedding. &nbsp;Here at Litha, we celebrate his fulfillment! &nbsp;It is too soon to harvest, that will be soon enough. &nbsp;But it is a good time to look at what the baby born at Yule has grown to become!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">And here is Litha's gift to us, as expressed in a reading which came from a place which you might not have expected. &nbsp;But the point of that reading was that someone was given something that they didn't put to use, and here at Litha we celebrate someone's fulfillment. &nbsp;In other words, the baby born at Yule now has all he needs to carry out what he needs to do.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">So much of theology deals with stories of people who were trying to get what was already theirs. &nbsp;And some of us surprise ourselves when we discover how much we have.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">And so let's celebrate this, and learn!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: small;">Blessed Be!&nbsp;</span></p>]]></description>
